Former rap musician Joey Boy is now a monk who takes Father Teng's place at his rural temple, where a crisis develops involving a nearby stone quarry.
Two new monks, one of them a former rock music star seeking inner peace, join a temple plagued by thieves who are stealing its valuable holy relics.
In the forests of Karnataka, a farmer and his community face eviction from the land when they get caught in the currents of socio-political change.
Determined to trace her ancestral history, an Armenian woman travels to a French village, where she befriends a kind man and, better yet, finds herself.
Determined to prove herself as a street dancer, Maria heads from juvie to a Bronx rec center where she's introduced to her dance idol, Honey Daniels.
Despite discouragement from her loved ones, a talented street dancer tries out for an exclusive dance crew in a bid to win a college scholarship.
Fresh off a top-secret training, feisty heroine Little Red teams up with intrepid reporter Wolf to investigate the disappearance of Hansel and Gretel.
A multigenerational household navigates daily life, evolving relationships and clashes between old and new mindsets in this light family drama.
When a teen with terminal cancer miraculously finds herself in remission, she struggles to give up the attention her illness gave her at school.
The remarkable true story of Gift Ngoepe, the first African to play for Major League Baseball, is recounted in this inspiring documentary.
Accused of murder, Ig Perish wakes up one day to find he's grown a set of horns – compelling people to confess their sins to him.
On a dare, seven college friends spend a night at an abandoned hotel rumored to be haunted and find themselves trapped in a nightmare.
Follow the eerie story of Father Malachi Martin, a disenchanted priest whose belief in demonic possession would lead him to conduct several exorcisms.
Witnesses recount the shocking 1996 hostage crisis in Lima, Peru, where rebels held scores of high-level figures captive at an ambassador's residence.
After a long career battling the Cheyenne, a U.S. Army captain is ordered to safely escort the tribe's most influential chief to his Montana homeland.
Two teenage geeks inadvertently find a lifelike, state-of-the-art sex robot, but must dodge the high-profile owner who lost her in order to keep her.
When a resourceful but flighty Londoner is threatened with eviction, she vows to do whatever it takes to defeat a greedy real estate agent.
Andy Samberg stars in this comedy as an accident-prone daredevil who's determined to jump 15 buses on his moped and impress his abusive stepfather.
A motivated teen strives to rise from dishwasher to waiter at a luxury hotel only to tread in the abusive tide of its workplace hierarchy.
It's love at first sight for Dracula when he meets Ericka, the charming but mysterious captain of the monster cruise that Mavis plans for the family.

Titles: House at the End of the Street
Description: Moving to a new town proves even more stressful for a teenager when she learns that the house next door was the site of a double murder.
Featuring archival footage and exclusive interviews, this documentary looks at the rise, fall and comeback of charismatic fashion designer Zac Posen.
Blending fact with myth, this conspiracy-minded docufiction argues that the U.S. purchased Yugoslavia's secret space program in the 1960s.

Titles: How the Beatles Changed the World
Description: Interviews and rare archival footage illuminate how the Beatles' influence over music and culture continues to be felt around the world.
The Grinch decides to rob Whoville of Christmas – but a dash of kindness from little Cindy Lou Who and her family may be enough to melt his heart.

Titles: How to Be a Latin Lover
Description: When an aging Lothario gets the boot from his sugar mama, he must pull out all the stops to find a new female sponsor.
Dray lives life one woman at a time and is the envy of all his friends, until his sister decides to show him the error of his philandering ways.
In the 1970s, a group of activists who gathered to protest nuclear testing formed the iconic Greenpeace environmental organization.

Titles: How to Make an American Quilt
Description: A conflicted young woman spends the summer with her grandmother, her great-aunt and their quilting circle, whose life stories captivate her.

Titles: How to Win the US Presidency
Description: This whimsical look at rough-and-tumble American politics examines the influence of money, religion and even ancient Rome on presidential campaigns.
A schoolteacher known for his good deeds and benevolence takes a walk on the dark side after undergoing a heart transplant.
This action-packed animated double feature pits the Hulk against two of the Marvel Universe's most powerful characters: Wolverine and Thor.
A scheming matriarch plots to cut off her disabled stepson and his wife from the family fortune, creating a division within the clan.
Two kindred spirits who are betrothed to others must decide whether to go through with arranged marriages or brush aside convention for true love.
While filming his daily life for a media course, Cowen discovers his small English town may be under an ominous and otherworldly influence.
U.S. Border Patrol agent and deadly hunter Jim Rhodes takes violent revenge when a group of desperate thieves kidnaps his daughter after a robbery.
A hired gun has second thoughts when he's contracted to kill a teenage girl whose father's shady business dealings put her life in danger.
Fired for being gay, schoolteacher Richard returns in drag as force-of-nature Bianca, gets hired for the same job and plots sweet, scornful revenge.

Titles: Hurricane Bianca: From Russia With Hate
Description: When Texas teacher Richard is lured to Russia under false pretenses by his enemy Deb, his drag alter ego Bianca soon turns the country upside down.
A pimp with aspirations of grandeur wants to make it as a rapper but discovers that fame isn't all it's cracked up to be in this indie drama.
A young actress rehearsing for a play about human trafficking begins to relive terrifying scenes that may be dreams – or an alternate reality.
Four individuals in modern India grapple with their identities amid social taboos, trauma and brutal sexual discrimination in this quartet of stories.
Mixing archival footage with present-day interviews, Olympic champion and global icon Usain Bolt opens up about his athletic legacy.
This intense documentary follows real cases of American girls enslaved in the child sex trade through ads in a newspaper's online classified section.
Through her own words and art, a young woman details the healing power of yoga in her struggle with anorexia and her journey to self-acceptance.
To qualify for an apartment reserved for singles, a married couple stages a divorce. But when her husband unexpectedly remarries, Li seeks justice.
A North Korean propagandist who escaped to Seoul now creates satirical art about Kim Jong Il's regime and copes with repercussions of his defection.
After learning that an ex-military friend and his parents were killed, the highly trained John Gold comes to town seeking answers and revenge.
Hell-bent on avenging his wife's murder, Stanley Hill summons an old partner's help in exposing a cover-up by crooked cops and slimy politicians.

Titles: I Don't Know How She Does It
Description: In this affable yuppie comedy, Kate Reddy is a successful executive, wife and mom whose personal and professional lives hang in precarious balance.
Experience the joy and sacrifice of one of the nation's premier dance companies as its members and instructors prepare for a prestigious competition.

Titles: I Fine... Thank You... Love You
Description: Desperate to go to the U.S. to win back his girlfriend, Yim hires a tutor to teach him English. But things don't go according to plan.
While fighting for his welfare benefits following a job-ending heart attack, a widowed carpenter befriends a single mother in a similar plight.

Titles: I'll See You in My Dreams
Description: After the passing of her dog, a long-widowed senior citizen is in need of companionship. Two very different possibilities present themselves.

Titles: I'm in Love with a Church Girl
Description: When a tough-minded ex-drug dealer falls for a beautiful but highly devout woman, their mutual attraction takes them both down a twisty path.
This film explores the controversial role of ice hockey "enforcers," as well as the physical and mental price paid by the game's notorious tough guys.
Four hundred years after they were frozen in time, a Ming Dynasty guard and his three pursuers are defrosted to continue their ancient battle.
After an actor is hit by a car driven by the police commissioner's sister, his scheming brother-in-law files a bogus suit against the commissioner.
Igor, the brilliant but deformed assistant to mad Dr. Glickenstein, dreams of winning the Evil Science Fair and the heart of village beauty Gretchen.
"Last Comic Standing" winner Iliza Shlesinger unleashes her acerbic, stream-of-conscious comedy on an unsuspecting audience in her hometown of Dallas.
Work problems are piling up for a businessman. But when he discovers a pathway to his daughter's imaginary world, he starts finding some solutions.
This anthology illustrates the timeless nature of desire in four stories of incest, bloodlust and other forbidden subjects.
A naive and sheltered young woman embarks on a whimsical adventure across Italy in the hopes of meeting director Federico Fellini.
With little oxygen left in their scuba tanks, two sisters are trapped in a shark cage at the bottom of the ocean while great whites circle nearby.
Grief-stricken over the death of his true love, singer-songwriter Metin has given up on life, until he meets Gizem, who slowly reawakens his heart.
When an imprisoned terrorist cell hijacks a high-security prison in outer space, a CIA agent becomes the one chance of stopping them.
A man returns to his childhood hometown, where he meets the happily married woman he once jilted, while his best friend endures a more volatile union.
A couple trying to conceive invite a woman with a mysterious past to move in with them. But it's an invitation they might come to regret.
In the streets of Senegal, a youth movement rises up against a regime bent on retaining power in this chronicle of the nation's stormy 2012 elections.
When Elastigirl gets recruited for a high-profile crime-fighting mission, Mr. Incredible takes on his toughest assignment ever: full-time parenting.
A man buys a young girl, code-names her "Doll" and sends her to live with a mother of two who has a mysterious mission to be fulfilled.

Titles: Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull
Description: Indiana Jones is drawn into a Russian plot to unearth the Crystal Skulls of Akator, Amazonian artifacts with supernatural powers.

Titles: Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade
Description: Accompanied by his father, Indiana Jones sets off on his third adventure to explore the cradle of civilization on a perilous hunt for the Holy Grail.

Titles: Indiana Jones and the Raiders of the Lost Ark
Description: When Indiana Jones is hired by the government to locate the legendary Ark of the Covenant, he finds himself up against the entire Nazi regime.

Titles: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom
Description: Indiana Jones, his young sidekick and a spoiled songbird get more than they bargained for when they go to India in search of a missing magical stone.
After a weekend fling with artist Victor, Veronica, a psychiatrist and politician's wife, becomes the target of Victor's dangerous romantic obsession.
Former U.S. Labor Secretary Robert Reich makes a compelling case about the serious crisis the U.S. faces due to the widening economic gap.
Italians in London reveal the ups and downs of immigration and touch upon their uneasiness about leaving behind their crisis-ridden homeland.
A Jewish cinema owner in occupied Paris is forced to host a Nazi premiere, where a group of American soldiers called the Basterds plans a face-off.
Unbeknownst to his 12-year-old daughter, a bookbinder has a secret ability to bring characters to life by reading their stories out loud.
A grieving policeman and a rickshaw driver are brought together by a dark, tragic secret that will change their lives forever.
Unable to locate the elusive mother of a baby girl left on his doorstep, an Acapulco playboy unexpectedly begins to develop feelings for the tot.
Five viral Internet celebrities travel to a competition that will award one of them their own television series in this ensemble comedy.
In the near future, two frightened sisters fight for survival after losing their father during a deadly, quietly looming apocalypse.

Titles: Inuyasha the Movie - L'isola del fuoco scarlatto
Description: Ai, a young half-demon who has escaped from Horai Island to try to help his people, returns with potential saviors InuYasha, Sesshomaru and Kikyo.

Titles: Inuyasha the Movie - La spada del dominatore del mondo
Description: The Great Dog Demon beaqueathed one of the Three Swords of the Fang to each of his two sons. Now the evil power of the third sword has been awakened.

Titles: InuYasha: The Movie 2: The Castle Beyond the Looking Glass
Description: With their biggest foe seemingly defeated, InuYasha and his friends return to everyday life. But the peace is soon shattered by an emerging new enemy.
After the end of apartheid, newly elected President Nelson Mandela uses the 1995 World Cup rugby matches to unite his people in South Africa.
Artists and writers delve into the heart of Antoine de Saint-Exupéry's timeless fable, which captured the imagination of children and adults worldwide.
At an initiation ritual for the young men of his Xhosa community, a closeted factory hand meets a Johannesburg teen who discovers his best-kept secret.
A boy with a hearing and speech impairment – and extraordinary athletic ability – chases his lifelong dream of playing cricket for India.
Bored in their happy marriage, a couple decides to spice things up by fighting more, but their game takes the relationship on an unexpected path.

Titles: Iron Cowboy: The Story of the 50.50.50
Description: A record-setting triathlete dares to complete 50 Ironman races – a 2.4-mile swim, a 112-mile bike ride, and a 26.2-mile run – in 50 days in 50 states.

Titles: Iron Man & Captain America: Heroes United
Description: While battling to keep the Red Skull and Taskmaster from unleashing a Hydra army, Iron Man and Captain America must learn to work together.
A young millionaire is willing to do anything to make the schoolteacher he loves happy. Even if it means helping her marry someone else.
Two young lovers in Banaras are caught in the crossfire of a feud between their powerful families and a political climate destroying their city.
The Olsen twins put a cute new spin on Mark Twain's classic tale "The Prince and the Pauper," playing identical 9-year-olds from very different backgrounds: orphaned Amanda and wealthy Alyssa.
When a beautiful belly-dancer moves into their apartment building, a group of unhappily married men strives to get her attention.
When Eva and Alex decide to wed in England, where they met three years earlier, obstacles including a labor strike and a volcano keep them apart.
Two down-on-their-luck singers set out to marry wealthy women – but not everyone is happy to have them climb the social ladder.
This unfiltered documentary follows the rocky life and stratospheric career of Allen Iverson, an NBA icon who left an indelible mark on the sport.
Miniforce, a special task force of elite rangers, takes on the Lizard Army to save Earth before it’s too late, in this prequel to the TV series.

Titles: Jaan-E-Mann: Let's Fall in Love... Again
Description: To avoid alimony payments, an aspiring actor schemes for his ex-wife to marry an unlikely suitor, but soon realizes he may not be ready to lose her.
Equipped with a mechanical heart and determined to stay out of death's shadow, young Jack understands that love could prove fatal.
Once upon a time, baseball cards were as much an American pastime as the sport. But then scandal rocked the multi-million-dollar industry for good.
Ken Bruen's bestselling crime novels leap to life in this series of TV movies featuring Irish cop-turned-private-investigator Jack Taylor.
When an aging flight attendant's caught smuggling cash and forced to help with an investigation, she hatches a clever plan to make off with the dough.
A lottery ticket salesperson faces an ethical dilemma after setting aside a soon-to-be winning ticket for a customer to pick up and pay for later.
Incarcerated for a crime he didn’t commit, a young man must navigate the crowded, cut-throat environment of prison as he awaits trial.
A gifted young man from a drought-stricken village helps a group of ecologists find water for migrating flamingoes.
When they travel to their father's ancestral village, city kids expecting a natural paradise instead find a poor, dusty town that harbors secrets.
After 11 years in Canada, young Meena returns to her native Pakistan for a family wedding and becomes romantically entangled with an adopted cousin.

Titles: Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back
Description: Jay and Silent Bob's comic book alter egos have been sold to Hollywood without permission, so they head to Tinseltown to sabotage the production.
Tormented by mistrust, a businessman hires a cagey tailor to track his wife's whereabouts with her doctor only to send his mind further down an abyss.
The journey of fashion designer Jeremy Scott from humble roots on a Missouri farm to creative director of Moschino is charted in this documentary.
Adapted from the hit Broadway musical, this nostalgic look at the Four Seasons and their bumpy offstage lives stretches across four decades.
Host Hugh Bonneville traces Jesus' last days to learn how the execution of an itinerant Jewish preacher had an immense impact on society.
The story of famed L.A. nightclub Catch One and owner Jewel Thais-Williams, who defied all odds and provided a safe space for black LGBT communities.
Jimi Hendrix's family, friends, and fellow musicians discuss his life and influence. Hendrix also appears in classic performance footage.
This documentary profiles sushi chef Jiro Ono, an 85-year-old master whose 10-seat, $300-a-plate restaurant is legendary among Tokyo foodies.

Titles: Jis Desh Men Ganga Behti Hai
Description: Falling in with a band of outlaws during a holy pilgrimage, a country boy tries to change their violent ways ahead of a showdown with the authorities.

Titles: Joe Cocker: Mad Dog with Soul
Description: From his star turn at Woodstock to his battles with addiction, this film chronicles the stormy life and unique talent of soulful singer Joe Cocker.
Truth and fiction blend in this quasi-documentary about six exhausted workers at a Mumbai call center servicing U.S. customers.
One minute, Civil War veteran John Carter is evading Apaches; the next, he's waking up on Mars, a once-fruitful planet that's devolved into chaos.
A bank manager and his wife, still grieving over their daughter who died in a fire, become pawns in a bank heist with ties to corruption and fraud.
Two siblings share a body, each getting it for 12 hours a day. But when one of them breaks the rules, their whole way of life comes crashing down.
In 1806, ambitious magician Norrell leads a revival of practical magic in England and ignites a fierce rivalry with bold young conjurer Strange.
The wounds of a traumatic childhood and a corrupt, unjust system push a young man into becoming a cold-blooded, ruthless gangster.
Separated at birth, a pair of identical twins unexpectedly reunite as adults and embark on a madcap mission to take down a common enemy from their past.

Titles: Judy Moody and the Not Bummer Summer
Description: In this family film, never-dull third-grader Judy Moody embarks on a summer adventure with her brother, Stink, and always-up-for-fun Aunt Opal.
Following the stories of five diverse individuals, this documentary offers a glimpse into the indomitable tenacity of several Mumbai residents.
In this heartwarming tale, Julie Powell decides to spice up her uneventful life by cooking all 524 recipes outlined in Julia Child's classic cookbook.
After a whirlwind romance, a couple rushes to say "I do" at the bride's family estate on Martha's Vineyard, where their relations meet — and clash.
When a big-city art dealer travels to North Carolina to meet her new husband's small-town family, their trip gives rise to a multitude of problems.
A young impoverished woman learns she's been predestined to change the fate of the universe after a genetically engineered hunter tracks her down.
Years after high school, a once-portly nice guy comes home for the holidays and reunites with a former crush he still has feelings for.
Slick lawyer Sung fears he's been cursed with bad karma and considers giving up his practice – until he's approached by a widow accused of murder.
Teen idol Justin Bieber provides personal snapshots from throughout his career, culminating with scenes from his triumphant 2010 concert tour.
On board Russia's first nuclear ballistic submarine, Capt. Vostrikov must race against time to prevent a Chernobyl-like explosion.
The happy life of a young blind couple is shattered when the wife is raped and corrupt police won't help, sending the husband on a quest for revenge.
Star-crossed lovers from different social strata struggle to overcome differences in class and family expectation, as well as a long separation.
Jailed for robbing his brother’s unscrupulous employer, a simpleton has a transformation while in prison, emerging with a violent mission for revenge.
An aggressive, wayward fisherman abandons his wife and daughters, who grow up to face the consequences of their father's mistakes.
In this Hindi version of the Tamil blockbuster, a Tamil gang leader in Kuala Lumpur seeks justice for crimes committed against him and his family.
While visiting India for her cousin's wedding, a Canadian girl develops strong feelings for a boy from a lower caste.

Directors: Roger Allers, Gaëtan Brizzi, Paul Brizzi, Joan C. Gratz, Mohammed Saeed Harib, Tomm Moore, Nina Paley, Bill Plympton, Joann Sfar, Michael Socha
Description: A troubled young girl and her mother find solace on a journey with a subversive poet whose words captivate their hearts and imaginations.
A popular singer on the run poses as a bartender and falls in love with a prostitute, but their love is threatened by a violent incident in his past.
A quiet ex-con's tenuous grip on reality starts to slip when his manipulative mother brings out a part of him he hoped to leave behind.
A scientist trying to solve one of the universe's greatest puzzles begins a romance with a much younger colleague that's haunted by a dark secret.
When flashbacks reveal that he's the reincarnation of a man murdered by his wife, rock star Monty sets out to get revenge for the decades-old crime.
A present-day woman takes responsibility for guiding a charming time-traveling 19th-century nobleman through the 21st century.
Secretly in love with his neighbor, a mild-mannered clerk is heartbroken when his much bolder, more charming friend wins her heart instead.
Outspoken comedian Katt Williams pokes fun at a variety of topics, including sex, relationships, parenthood and trying to make it as an entertainer.
When a late poet leaves behind his property to a young man, the man's brother suspects the poet may have been more than just a family friend.
Wrongfully accused of murder, two students' last hope lies with their defense attorney, an inexperienced bumbler who's never even tried a case.
Ken Burns's documentary depicts the action of famous Civil War battles, and relates the stories of soldiers, generals and a beleaguered president.

Titles: Ken Burns: The Roosevelts: An Intimate History
Description: Award-winning documentarian Burns profiles three members of one of America's premier political families: Theodore, Franklin and Eleanor Roosevelt.

Titles: Kevin Hart: Laugh at My Pain
Description: Sometimes edgy and always hilarious, comedian Kevin Hart shines in this theatrical version of his record-breaking 2011 live tour.
Philadelphia funnyman Kevin Hart takes the stage in front of a sold-out crowd at Madison Square Garden, part of his hit "Let Me Explain" world tour.
With his unique hip-hop style delivery, African American stand-up comedian Kevin Hart expounds on life at a sold-out concert performance.

Titles: Kevyn Aucoin: Beauty & the Beast in Me
Description: Makeup artist Kevyn Aucoin worked with top supermodels in the 1980s and 1990s. Personal videos merged with interviews provide a peek into his life.
A prison guard goes undercover as a dancer to try and recapture an escaped criminal and restore her police inspector boyfriend's reputation.
A cranky control freak must rely on his comically dysfunctional family to pull off a scam on a greedy land shark who's stolen his prized property.
A strict matriarch's regimented household is upended by the arrival of a spunky relative who challenges the rules.
While playing matchmaker to a pair of their friends, two young university students begin developing feelings for each other.
A 15-year-old girl with autism attempts to write a mystery novel based on her hunt for the killer of a neighborhood cat.
Sloan's vow to never return to Thailand is cut short when he's kidnapped and taken to a Thai prison, where he's forced to fight a 400-pound brute.
After a skilled fighter falls in the ring, his younger brother emerges from the shadows to train and get revenge against a brutal champion.
After graduating, four college roomies – petrified by the prospect of facing "real life" – reluctantly step into adulthood in this ensemble comedy.
Growing up in poverty and political turmoil, he found his way out in the ring. The early years of world-famous boxer Manny Pacquiao unfolds in this biopic.
When beer magnate Alfred "Freddy" Heineken is kidnapped in 1983, his abductors make the largest ransom demand in history.
An assassin is shot by her ruthless employer, Bill, and other members of their assassination circle. But she lives – and plots her vengeance.
The Bride has three left on her rampage list: Budd, Elle Driver and Bill himself. But when she arrives at Bill's house, she's in for a surprise.
On a remote island, elite soldiers discover their training exercise is actually an experimental death trap teeming with efficiently lethal robots.

Titles: Kill Hitler! The Luck of the Devil
Description: From politicians to officers, many attempted to kill Hitler – and failed. This documentary delves into the details of how their plots unraveled.
Posing as a telecom salesman at a business conference, a CIA agent fights to protect a fledgling Eastern European democracy from a military coup.
This true crime tale charts the rise and fall of mobster Danny Greene, who faced down the Mafia to gain control of organized crime in 1970s Cleveland.
An alien band of killer clowns descends from the cosmos to harvest scores of small-town victims, cocooning their prey in cotton candy to eat later.
After a whirlwind romance, Jen and Spencer settle into married life — until Spencer's secret past as a hit man shakes up their suburban bliss.
Two young men with disabilities befriend a hitman in a wheelchair and become his helpers, only to wind up in the crosshairs of a Serbian mobster.
On patrol in Afghanistan, a British paratrooper unit unwittingly ventures into a dry riverbed that turns out to be littered with land mines.
Already coping with a bully, a mercurial older brother and summer school, 15-year-old Jack is saddled with his young cousin for an eventful weekend.

A wealthy, despicable businessman comes to the realization that he may lose half his fortune to the obnoxious wife he's trying to divorce. So, he decides to arrange his own kidnapping in order to wipe himself out and claim poverty.
Meet the astonishing animals and adventurous people living on some of the most spectacular – and formidable – mountain ranges in the world.
After a bowler loses his hand, his career takes a nosedive. That is, until he uncovers the next big thing: an Amish kid named Ishmael.
A foster mom and her houseful of kids befriend a bitter neighbor after the Rodney King verdict is handed down in 1992 Los Angeles.

Directors: Abbas Alibhai Burmawalla, Mastan Alibhai Burmawalla
Description: A man's decision to marry three women, to keep them from committing suicide, complicates his relationship with his girlfriend.
A forensic psychologist teams up with an escaped kidnapping victim to hunt down a serial killer who abducts and dominates strong-willed women.
A field hockey-playing pizza delivery boy finds himself transformed from slacker to zombie slayer during an outbreak of the undead in Kuala Lumpur.
A devoted husband and father on his own for the weekend has his life turned inside out after giving shelter to two young women during a storm.
Though culturally insensitive by modern standards, this propaganda film examines the history of Japan from the 16th century through the 1930s.
An MIT astrophysics professor and his son unearth a string of numbers from a time capsule that seem to reveal a cataclysm that will wipe out humanity.
Witness the incredible, decades-long friendship between Koko the gorilla and Penny Patterson, who taught Koko to communicate via sign language.
With five loyal friends in tow, explorer Thor Heyerdahl sails a fragile balsa wood raft along an ancient path some 4,300 miles across the Pacific.
A speech and hearing-impaired couple persists through unforgiving obstacles to be accepted by society and live a life of dignity.
When he sets out to avenge his son's murder, mild-mannered snowplow driver Nils sparks a war between a Norwegian mobster and his Serbian rival.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Battle of Wits
Description: An artisan is cheated of his payment, a lion of his throne and a brother of his inheritance in these three stories of deception and justice.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Best Friends Forever
Description: A cat, monkey and donkey team up to narrate folktales about friendship from Northeast India, and the Indian regions of Bihar and Rajasthan.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Comics of India
Description: In three comic-strip-style tales, a boy tries to sell wisdom, a demon is released from captivity, and a king assigns impossible tasks to his minister.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Face Your Fears
Description: In three tales about fear, a baby elephant gets captured by a circus, two boys enter a haunted house and a parrot faces his fear of flying.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Oversmartness Never Pays
Description: A cat, monkey and donkey learn the consequences of cheating through stories from the Indian regions of Rajasthan, West Bengal and Maharashtra.

Titles: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: The Greatest Trick
Description: The consequences of trickery are explored in stories involving an inconsiderate husband, two greedy courtiers, and a kind man who loses everything.
After 10 years away from her family, Krisha returns for Thanksgiving, but bitter grudges and troubling addictions threaten to ruin the event.
Opting to stay on campus over the Thanksgiving holiday, coed Justine and a handful of friends find their break violently disrupted by a sadistic gang.
A kid with a heart condition falls for an ex-stripper with a lot of baggage and joins her Alcoholics Anonymous group to catch her attention.

Titles: Kuldip Patwal: I Didn't Do It!
Description: Accused of killing a politician, a local grocer’s fight to prove his innocence reveals his lifelong struggles with injustice leading up to the incident.
Sing, a mobster in 1940s China, longs to be as cool as the formally clad Axe Gang, a band of killers who rule Hong Kong, but can only pretend.
Shortsighted curmudgeon Mr. Magoo and his young nephew, Justin, fight such nefarious foes as kung fu villains, robot spiders and teenage mutants.
As preparations for the Winter Feast build, Po is caught between his obligations as the Dragon Warrior and his family holiday traditions.
Two mismatched archaeologists battle a team of vicious mercenaries in a race to discover an ancient Tibetan treasure of unimaginable worth.
A young woman talented at traditional dance finds her life changed when her love for a man clashes with the wishes of her father.
This film charts Nirvana's Kurt Cobain's rise to fame, his drug-addled romance with Courtney Love and the conspiracy theories surrounding his death.
When a recently single psychologist moves to a new neighborhood, she finds friendship with women starting to rebel against years of domestic abuse.
A young university student's world is shaken after her brief involvement with a wealthy playboy results in her pregnancy.

Titles: Kygo: Live at the Hollywood Bowl
Description: Join Norwegian electronic music superstar Kygo onstage and behind the scenes as he performs at the famed L.A. venue with a bevy of special guests.
Cinematic lovebirds Aishwarya Rai and Vivek Oberoi star in this love story about a sweet young girl, Diya, brought up by her widowed father on a coffee plantation in the village of Coorg.
Three best buddies are thrown into a wild chase for a priceless painting that was stolen from a house they used to throw a huge party.
Previously unseen footage is shaped into a fresh and timely retelling of the 1992 Rodney King trial – and the verdict that sparked civil unrest.
The plane crash that killed Buddy Holly also took Ritchie Valens, whose modest upbringing and rise to fame are depicted in this exhilarating biopic.
After winning a shared trip to a soccer match, two colleagues who hold opposite world views find they're stuck traveling together for the duration.
Beautiful and ruthless Griselda Blanco, known as the queen of cocaine, becomes Pablo Escobar's boss and governs a world of deceit and death.
Eager for cash, Rajesh joins his friend Shankar's blood-theft operation. As Rajesh's greed grows and the cops close in, Shankar is poised to explode.
When a family moves into an upscale housing development, they encounter a series of paranormal events that drive them to the edge of insanity.
An American travels to Hong Kong in hopes of winning a lucrative – but potentially deadly – all-female underground fighting tournament.
When an apartment building manager discovers a water nymph in the complex's swimming pool, he tries to help her return to her mythical home.
Industrial workers struggle against the greed of their employers and the apathy of the government toward the conditions in which they live and work.
An ex-CIA contractor turned thief is forced to head a CIA gambit to infiltrate a black ops Mexican prison and steal $50 million in drug cartel money.
Seeking romance and friendship, a young gay lawyer travels to Fire Island in the off-season and is soon on the run after witnessing a murder.
A nobleman who values his people's well-being over his emperor's edicts is killed. His knights vow revenge.
During an evening apart, married couple Joanna and Michael encounter tempting opportunities to cheat on each other with sexy acquaintances.
After a blackmailing scandal and being sidelined from the French national team, Real Madrid forward Karim Benzema tells his side of the story.
This documentary retraces the footsteps of Adolf Hitler's mysterious nephew and explores what became of the Hitler family line.
Anna chooses February 29 to propose marriage to her boyfriend, but after meeting a charming innkeeper, she must evaluate her original plans.

In this entertaining installment of the wildly popular early-learning series, Professor Quigley, Leap, Lily and Tad arrive at the magical Letter Factory, where jumbles of sounds are miraculously shaped into letters.
With transport support from their magic car, Axel, the LeapFrog pets make a new friend named Max, who helps them learn counting skills in Numberland.
Scout takes a magical trip to a farm where an alligator and other friendly critters teach him all about sounding out the letters of the alphabet.
Using rhythm and rhymes, a funky band and a colorful cast of characters help make reading, sounding out vowels and building words easy and fun!
The spirit of a murdered woman contacts four bachelors, enlisting their help to find her killer.
After millions of people on Earth suddenly disappear, a pilot flying a plane stuck at 30,000 feet must find a way to ensure the passengers' survival.

Titles: Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole
Description: Soren, a barn owl kidnapped from his peaceful forest home, is brought to an orphanage where he must train to become a soldier.
A petty thief teams up with two bickering accomplices to safeguard a powerful relic and save humankind from a tribe of vengeful, winged humanoids.
Three assassins – magician Lei Ying, hit man Tieh Hon and kung fu master Ti Tan – are sent to Yunnan by their clan leader to bring to justice another clan member who betrayed the tribe.
A motley crew of apocalypse survivors living at an abandoned truck stop never suspects that the pregnant woman among them is carrying the Messiah.

Titles: Lego Friends: Girls on a Mission
Description: Five best friends put their teamwork, wits and courage to the test when they take on a mission to protect Heartlake City from bad people.

Titles: LEGO House - Home of the Brick
Description: In Billund, Denmark, a nearly 130,000-square-foot house is constructed with 25 million Lego bricks, capturing the awe of kids of all ages.
Eschewing the carnivorous ways of his fellow lions, maverick Leo follows a vegetarian diet – causing the other lions to shun him.

Titles: Les Bleus - Une autre histoire de France, 1996-2016
Directors: Pascal Blanchard, Sonia Dauger, David Dietz
Description: This documentary charts 20 years of the French national soccer team, Les Bleus, whose ups and downs have mirrored those of French society.
Some returning combat veterans suffer scars that are more psychological than physical. This film follows patients and staff during their treatment.
Destiny brings Mecnun and Leyla together as newborns, and again years later. Despite unexpected turns in Mecnun's zany life, Leyla remains a constant.
A young woman's attempt to come out of the closet on Thanksgiving gets complicated when her male roommate shows up to her parents' home unannounced.
Following the death of his beloved girlfriend, Beth, Zach is first shattered and then overjoyed when she inexplicably comes back to life.
A couple operates a bustling dog rescue out of their own home, vowing to give a safe space to the neediest pups on the planet – 10,000 and counting.
A shapeshifter has to kill, then inhabit his victims, or die. But as his need for new bodies speeds up, he finally faces down his own mortality.
Johnnie To's character-centered drama follows a Hong Kong firefighting crew as they take on harrowing rescue missions and navigate personal dilemmas.
Over 50 years of their lives, a couple enjoys the blessings and setbacks of parenting, and learns that God has to be at the center of their family.
When Pedro marries her sister, Tita throws herself into her cooking – and discovers she can transfer her emotions through the food she prepares.
After each of them loses a child to murder, two women who meet in a support group initiate their own investigation when the police are no help.
Director Steven Spielberg takes on the towering legacy of Abraham Lincoln, focusing on his stewardship of the Union during the Civil War years.
Kidnapped as a child and raised in the circus, a young lion tamer’s tough side emerges when he gets entangled in an underworld murder mystery.

Titles: Listen Up! The Lives of Quincy Jones
Description: Steering clear of convention, this affecting documentary pays tribute to the life and work of composer, musician and producer Quincy Jones, one of the best-known and most respected men in the music industry.
Seeking to improve his combat skills, a young man falls in love with a woman with mystical powers, but his past stands in the way of their union.

Titles: Little Lunch: The Halloween Horror Story
Description: When the class puts on a Halloween play about a boy who leaves behind his friends for a scary new place, it hits too close to home for one student.

Titles: Little Lunch: The Nightmare Before Graduation
Description: Mrs. Gonsha's students are excited about the end of primary school – until they discover that a classmate might not move on with them.
Jake and Tony become friends when Jake's dad inherits a home above Tony's mother's shop. Friendship is tested when Jake's dad raises the shop's rent.
The devil sends his sweet son Nicky to Earth to bring back his scheming siblings, who have plans to oust dear old dad from power.

Titles: Little Singham aur Kaal ka Mahajaal
Description: When Kaal, the vilest demon on earth, threatens to destroy his village, child cop Little Singham must use his strength and smarts to fight back.
Little Singham is in London to meet the queen, but when the famed Kohinoor Diamond gets stolen, the kid cop goes on a wild, citywide hunt for the thief.
A former Goth studying to become a nun finds her faith tested when she returns home to visit her brother, who has been disfigured in the Iraq War.
This made-for-TV drama chronicles the scandal and enduring mystery surrounding Lizzie Borden, who was tried in 1892 for axing her parents to death.

Titles: Lo and Behold: Reveries of the Connected World
Description: Filmmaker Werner Herzog presents a history of the internet, starting with its birth in 1969, and ponders the joys and sorrows of its social influence.

Titles: Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels
Description: Hoping to make a bundle in a high-stakes poker game, four shiftless lads from London's East End instead find themselves swimming in debt.
Over the space of 90 minutes, Ivan Locke's life spins out of control via a series of phone calls made while he drives down the highway to London.
A government agent wrongly accused of a crime gets a shot at freedom if he can engineer a high-risk rescue mission to outer space.
A young man and woman fall in love but are threatened to be torn apart by the tensions between their Latino and Caucasian communities in Arizona.
In the 23rd century, inhabitants of a domed city exist in a world filled with life's pleasures – but no one is allowed to live past the age of 30.
In this black comedy, an English professor marries his landlady to get closer to his forbidden obsession: her teenage daughter.
When his reclusive-banker lover disappears, a hard-partying young British hedonist plunges into the dangerous world of espionage to find the truth.
This documentary follows the 2016 tour of beloved rock band The Tragically Hip as they make their way across Canada one last time.
An officer killed on the job returns to Earth as a ghost to solve his own murder and seek justice with the help of a rookie cop and some funky magic.
When Adolf Hitler reawakens at the site of his former bunker 70 years later, he's mistaken for a brilliant comedian and becomes a media phenomenon.
Under a government initiative, a retired alcoholic soccer player is sent to establish a soccer team in a politically troubled area.
This documentary pays tribute to the young cadets who gave their lives to defend Mexico against U.S. forces during the battle of Chapultepec Castle.
Featuring never-before-seen images, personal testimonies and more, this is the story of one of the most notorious drug smugglers of all time.
This documentary recounts the feats of the Coxless Crew, a team of four women who rowed from San Francisco to Australia in support of two charities.

Titles: Love Dot Com: The Social Experiment
Description: Sparks fly and romance blooms when Shelby, a vegan chef, meets Greg, a developer – until their opposing views clash.

When the Hong Kong government enacts a ban on smoking cigarettes indoors, the new law drives hard-core smokers outside, facilitating a meeting between Cherie, a makeup saleswoman, and Jimmy, an advertising exec.
Not romantically inclined, a popular radio personality finds herself caught between two diametrically opposed suitors.
To prove himself to a love interest, a delivery boy learns dubious kung fu from an aging charlatan so he can challenge his archrival to a fight.
A charming hitman questions his profession after learning his next target is the karaoke singer he’s falling in love with.
Single coworkers at a radio station are brought together by mutual friends, but their starry-eyed notions about love may scuttle their romance.
A love triangle gets complicated when a female English tutor unknowingly gets between a hot-tempered guy and his off-to-the-United States girlfriend.
Over the years, as they come and go in each other's life, childhood pals Rosie and Alex struggle to resolve the lasting, intimate bond between them.
In this blend of documentary and dramatization, circumstances test notions of love held by a young stripper, a single-dad surfer and a teen musician.
An esteemed young poetry teacher at a Catholic boarding school risks everything when she engages in a feverish affair with a female student.
Struggling in a loveless marriage, a hard-drinking, workaholic cop finds a chance at redemption after a fateful incident leaves him wounded.
Known simply as "Lucha," field hockey player Luciana Aymar shares her tumultuous and triumphant journey to become the best in the world.
During an uprising in Russia's St. Petersburg, teen girl Lucky meets handsome Aditya, the Indian ambassador's son, and together they flee the chaos.
Haunted by disturbing visions, a workaholic takes a vacation with his family, but a detour leads them to an unsettling stranger and chilling events.
Three men from different nations must find their way out of the Amazon jungle – on foot – when they get lost on the way to Brazil's World Cup Final.
The relationship between a journalist and a lawyer she meets while investigating a story grows complicated as she uncovers layers of deception.
On his first visit to his home city of Kolkata in 13 years, a Paris-based chef is faced with a cooking challenge that will change his life forever.

Titles: Mac & Devin Go to High School
Description: Devin Overstreet may be the class valedictorian, but he hasn't had much life experience. Enter Mac Johnson, a 10th-year senior and weed dealer.
After relocating to a different town with her husband, a housewife begins to sense the existence of a mysterious presence in their new house.
In a post-apocalyptic future, a malicious gang murders Max's family as an act of retaliation, forcing Max to hit the open road seeking vengeance.
A woman joins the janitorial staff of the Federal Reserve Bank and conspires with two co-workers to pilfer old money that's scheduled to be destroyed.
This collection cherry-picks trailers, forgotten scenes and poster art from 47 gory oldies, including Bay of Blood and The Blood Spattered Bride.
A stockbroker struggling with bipolar disorder goes to live with his estranged father in a cramped flat, where old resentments bubble to the surface.
A bridge under construction collapses in Mumbai, killing a man's family and launching him on a crusade to bring those responsible to justice.
This documentary chronicles the rise of the footwear designer behind a billion-dollar empire and his subsequent comeback after a financial scandal.
Pregnant and overwhelmed, Diana hires a caretaker for her son with severe autism. But she soon begins to fear the new nanny has sinister intentions.
Originally polar opposites, an American fashion student and the daughter of an industry mogul form an everlasting bond and start a rock band in Milan.
Young Nicolas agrees to do Santa's work for one year. But the stress of the job threatens the boy's sense of joy – and Christmas itself.
Attracted to thrills across the globe, intrepid athletes venture to remote locations in pursuit of their extreme form of bliss.
This dramatic documentary explores the life and mind of Magnus Carlsen, the charismatic Norwegian prodigy who became world chess champion.
Two young brothers encounter a singing bird who treats them to a musical reinterpretation of one of India’s most epic ancient tales.
In this comedy, characters from all walks of life go head-to-head around the mahjong table in a high-stakes contest of different playing styles.
After lying to his girlfriend, orthopedic surgeon Samir must conjure up a pretend wife in this musical comedy.
When the son of a wealthy businessman and the daughter of a struggling engineer fall in love, the young man's parents question the girl's motives.
With their relationship running on autopilot, a discontent husband and wife must confront their issues while on a trip with the extended family.
After receiving a strange present, a professor and his pregnant wife are plagued by tragedy and a paranormal presence that's determined to kill.
In this kung fu tale set in Beijing, a young man armed with incomparable martial arts skills gets embroiled in the world of underground fight clubs.
A single woman seizes an opportunity when, while standing under a train station clock, she meets a stranger who mistakes her for his blind date.
Forbidden love, fraying loyalties and flagrant hypocrisy emerge when sanctimonious politicians drive a madam’s brothel from the heart of Hyderabad.
With the assistance of a psychiatrist, an acclaimed filmmaker struggles to come to terms with a mysterious romantic trauma.
A reclusive small-town locksmith who can't stop writing letters to a lost love meets a kindly bank teller who challenges him to look to the future.
Concerned that dementia will soon steal his most cherished memories, a Hindu doctor hires a Mulsim rickshaw driver to take him to his childhood home.
A filmmaker working on a documentary about love in modern Manhattan becomes personally entangled in the romantic lives of his subjects.

Titles: Manolo: The Boy Who Made Shoes for Lizards
Description: As legendary shoe designer Manolo Blahnik speaks about his creative process, his celebrity admirers chime in with their own takes on his work.
A poor heroine is sent to live with wealthy relatives in 1800s England, where her wit and writing talent find the room, and circumstance, to grow.
Four stories by writer Sadaat Hasan Manto culminate in a single gruesome drama that's set during the partitioning of the Indian subcontinent.
An Indian business owner struggles to keep his company afloat amid global competition while trying to make up for lost time with his family.
When criminal psychologist Kate Fuller investigates a man who was seemingly murdered in his sleep by his wife, she uncovers a case like no other.
A series of high-stakes thefts at banks owned by a manipulative millionaire sparks an FBI agent to suspect a sinister plan behind the deadly heists.

Titles: Mark Gatiss: A Study in Sherlock
Description: Mark Gatiss, who co-created “Sherlock” and plays Mycroft Holmes, discusses the show with Benedict Cumberbatch, Martin Freeman and others in the cast.
When his wife goes missing, university professor Saurabh remains at home while the police investigate, but his grip on reality loosens as days pass.
Fact meets fiction in this docudrama chronicling the journey of a spacecraft crew as it embarks in 2033 on a mission to colonize the red planet.
In ancient China, Zhi Ming trains at the legendary Northern Shaolin temple to avenge the death of his father at the hands of a nefarious magistrate.
This provocative film sheds light on actor-comedian Martin Lawrence's roots, his rise to fame and his walk on the wild side.

Titles: Martin Luther: The Idea that Changed the World
Description: This docudrama tells the dramatic story of the monk who took on the Catholic Church, tracing his life before and after the contentious "95 Theses."
This documentary reveals the cracks in India's anti-dowry act and gives voice to both women and men who've been victimized by the law's abusers.

Titles: Marvel & ESPN Films Present: 1 of 1: Genesis
Description: This documentary explores the connections between elite athletes and Marvel superheroes such as Spider Man, Black Widow and Captain America.

Titles: Marvel's Iron Man & Hulk: Heroes United
Description: When scientists join Hulk's gamma energy with Tony Stark's Arc Reactor, the resulting force creates a foe that only the two Marvel heroes can combat.
Ordinary girl Mary picks an extraordinary flower and travels to Endor College, a school for magic. But its foremost teachers have a sinister plan.
In 1930s London, Michael Banks and his three children get some help turning their topsy-turvy world around when his magical childhood nanny reappears.
A loving husband and father's joyful family life is rocked to its core upon the discovery that he has a young son borne from a past extramarital affair.
Needing hard evidence to convict a company chairman of fraud, an investigator bargains with the company's tech expert to turn over his boss's ledger.
A single man in his 30s overwhelmed by his domineering mother meets a lesbian couple willing to go to extreme lengths to have a child.
A jealous, possessive mother thinks she is competing with her new daughter-in-law for the affections of her overindulged son.
An aging jazz musician learns after his wife's death that she may have been unfaithful to him decades before.
A messaging app unites a mute prostitute, an unruly rich girl and a stormy young woman, three Hong Kong teens living in pain and excess.
A man's inability to conquer his personal insecurities and distrust of other people leads to problems with his on-again, off-again wife and their son.

Titles: Maya Angelou: And Still I Rise
Description: Poet and civil rights activist Maya Angelou is celebrated using her own words set over rare photographs and video illustrating her remarkable life.
Friends, family and political titans recall the impact of Atlanta's Maynard Jackson, the first African-American mayor of a major Southern city.
An orphan girl who has ambitions of marrying a rich man changes her identity to win the heart of a prominent businessman's son.
Hoping to pump up their sound, a punk band hires Pepe, a keyboardist with Down Syndrome, but tensions erupt when he steals the show with his talent.
Desperate to start a new life with his girlfriend, a teenage boy steals drug money from her father, who happens to be the town's corrupt lawman.
In New York's Little Italy, a low-level hoodlum wrestles with loyalty to his mobster uncle, his faith and his friendship with an inveterate gambler.
An elderly immigrant matriarch from Hong Kong finally begins to break out of her shell of isolation when she suspects her husband of infidelity.
In 1930s Poland, a powerful psychic steers a group of strangers toward a fated convergence that ensures survival for one and annihilation for others.

Titles: Meet the Trumps: From Immigrant to President
Description: Learn about Donald Trump's family history, including his immigrant grandfather's gold-rush enterprises and his dad's development of a property empire.
After recovering from a tragic experience, a young woman makes a journey to her father's homeland and falls in love with a kind-hearted doctor.
When Melvin and his friends gather for dinner, their casual conversation takes a sharp turn as they begin to disclose raw truths about themselves.
Hiding his own murderous past, a man suffering from Alzheimer's must protect his daughter from her boyfriend, who he suspects is also a serial killer.
Glimpse into the brain's vast potential for memorization through the eyes of four competitive memory athletes as they share techniques and insights.
A streetwise cop teams with a veteran government agent to work for a super-secret, extremely dapper team that monitors extraterrestrials on Earth.
Will Smith and Tommy Lee Jones reprise their roles as two highly secretive and unofficial government agents dealing with all things evil and alien.
A hedonistic soccer mom takes a voyage of self-discovery when she tries to reconnect with her son by returning his pet rock to a Mediterranean island.
In this fast-paced Indonesian thriller, a young martial arts master travels to Jakarta, where he saves an orphan from a human-trafficking ring.

Titles: Merry Men: The Real Yoruba Demons
Description: Four of the richest bachelors in Abuja, Nigeria enjoy a life of fast cars, palatial homes and female attention while concealing their true activities.
After a disgruntled man blames his Marathi heritage for his lack of his success, he is visited by Shivaji, a great medieval Marathi king.
When a terrorist escapes custody, MI-5 director Harry Pearce becomes the scapegoat. But the wily veteran still has some spycraft tricks up his sleeve.

Titles: Middle School: The Worst Years of My Life
Description: At Hills Village Middle School, budding cartoonist Rafe and best pal Leo challenge their uptight principal by breaking every rule in his handbook.
When his son exhibits supernatural powers, a father takes the youngster on the run to protect him from government authorities and religious fanatics.
Sean Penn stars in this biopic about Harvey Milk, the openly gay San Francisco politician who was murdered by a disgruntled city supervisor in 1978.
A nameless widow juggles multiple jobs to support her daughter’s decision to study abroad, only to discover that she has other plans.
U.S. hockey coach Herb Brooks unites a motley crew of college athletes and turns them into a force to be reckoned with at the 1980 Winter Olympics.
This remake of the classic Grimm tale follows fair-skinned Snow White on a quest to regain her royal throne with help from a team of shady dwarves.
A modern love story is connected to an ancient folk tale as star-crossed lovers from different social classes are kept apart by their families.
Herself a talented artist, O-Ei works with her father, Tetsuzo, later known as Hokusai, on the woodblock prints that would make Edo famous worldwide.
On a summer night in 1890 Ireland, the unsettled daughter of aristocrats coaxes her father's valet to seduce her, though he's engaged to their cook.
With their divorce set to become final on Christmas day, a couple must decide if they're really ready to throw in the towel on their relationship.
Explore how the mainstream media's often disparaging portrayals of women contribute to the under-representation of females in positions of leadership.
This uplifting documentary follows R&B singer Sharon Jones's battle with pancreatic cancer while keeping her band intact for a return to the stage.
Emotionally vulnerable teacher Rachel accompanies three students to a weekend drama competition and forms an unexpected bond with troubled teen Billy.

Titles: Mission Control: The Unsung Heroes of Apollo
Description: Combining archive footage with present-day interviews, this documentary explores how Apollo's mission control helped change the course of history.
As Hitler's Nazis threaten to take command of Britain's skies, a squadron of Polish pilots arrives to aid the Royal Air Force against a mutual enemy.
Two strangers meet by chance on a trip to Thailand and form a connection when they realize their former romantic partners ended up getting together.
A gambler mired in debt thinks another cardsharp may just be his good luck charm as the two head for New Orleans to buy into a high-stakes poker game.
After investing in a shady deal that quickly falls apart, a morally flexible real estate agent involves his wife in a dangerous recovery plan.
During the War of 1812, two Native Americans and their British ally are pursued into enemy territory by American soldiers thirsting for revenge.
A lethal game of cat and mouse stretches from the desert to Tinseltown after Hollywood bad boy Thomas runs afoul of a cunning and dangerous drifter.
A young boy's life shifts when he's sent to work at a mechanic's shop far from his suburban home until an opportunity forces him to make a tough choice.
Former Olympian Molly Bloom ran a high-stakes poker game for the stars – until her lofty lifestyle nearly sent her to prison.
In 1953, the women of Wellesley College are measured by how well they marry – until the arrival of a professor who threatens to upend the status quo.
Two corporate spies with a $5 million haul for selling secrets are held hostage by a thief, triggering a game of cat and mouse to gain the upper hand.
TV news reporter James Russell helps put small-time criminal Franklin Hatchett in jail, but turns to protecting Hatchett when he escapes from prison.
A talking monkey famous for his TV commercials dreams of breaking into real movies. But first he stumbles upon a brother and sister who need his help.
Seeking revenge on his employer, a lazy bank agent and his two dim-witted friends concoct an elaborate but flawed heist.
A family’s festive Halloween plans take a spooky turn when an evil witch's curse transforms the costumed clan into actual monsters.
It's a new school year at Monster High, and the little sister of Clawdeen Wolf, Howleen, is determined to be more fangtastic than ever.

Titles: Monster High: Boo York, Boo York
Description: Cleo is invited to a gala in the big city celebrating a magical comet and brings her best friends along. But the sinister Nefera has other plans.

Titles: Monster High: Escape from Skull Shores
Description: A swanky cruise veers off course for Lagoona and her friends when they're left stranded on Skull Shores, an island with a notorious beast.
When Frankie Stein travels back in time, a teen scientist follows her home into the present and causes a lab accident that creates four new monsters.
In their bid to win the Skulltimate Roller Maze championship, Monster High loses its star players, Clawd and Deuce, to injury.
Big changes are afoot at Monster High when administrators announce a merger with two other schools, designed to bring all monsters together.
Draculaura is whisked to Transylvania to be crowned vampire queen, but when she learns she's been duped, the search is on for the true royal heir.
After learning that monsters and "Normies" used to spend Halloween together, Frankie Stein and her pals rally both groups for a frightfully good time.
At a Monster High party, Lagoona and pals are sucked into the reef, where she'll have to come to terms with her flaws and confront an old frenemy.
Hearing that their old school is being haunted, Spectra Vondergeist and her pals head back to Monster High to get to the bottom of the scary spookery.

Titles: Monster High: New Ghoul at School
Description: Insecure new student Frankie Stein struggles to fit in at Monster High, where ultra-cool ghoul Cleo De Nile and hunky monster Deuce rule the roost.

Titles: Monster High: Scaris, City of Frights
Directors: Dustin McKenzie, Andrew Duncan, Audu Paden
Description: When Clawdeen gets a chance to study with a top fashion designer, she and her pals hop on a plane to Scaris, France, the city where screams come true.

Titles: Monster High: Why Do Ghouls Fall in Love?
Description: Draculaura's ghoulfriends have some suspicions about one of her two persistent suitors – but can they stop him before he steals her un-beating heart?
An office temp thinks she's found Mr. Right when she starts dating a handsome surgeon. But there's a problem standing in the way of everlasting bliss.
TV personality Monty Don visits France’s most famous gardens to dig up the influence of power, culture and passion on their conceptions and designs.
As he nears the end of a lonely three-year stint on the moon base Sarang, astronaut Sam Bell begins to hear and see strange things.
In a crime-infested Miami neighborhood, a gay African-American boy with a drug-addicted mother grows up with the help of a mentoring drug dealer.
A brain-addled war vet, a failing band manager and a Stanley Kubrick impersonator help the CIA construct an epic scam by faking the 1969 moon landing.
A railway stationmaster tries to cope with his wife's death, his estrangement from his son and the corrupt world in which he lives.
When his father moves from the U.S. to Heidelberg, Germany, an African American teenager struggles to find his place and pursue his hip-hop dreams.
This comic documentary follows the Mortified movement, a series of stage events where adults share awkward childhood moments in front of strangers.
Two communities in Mumbai get a final chance to compete with each other in the celebration of the iconic Ganesh Chaturthi festival.
Motu and Patlu want to help a circus lion get back to the jungle. On the way, the three become caught up in an exciting adventure in the forest.
Featuring breathtaking imagery and thought-provoking narration, this film takes viewers to the summits of some of the world’s most amazing mountains.

Directors: Peter Farrelly, Will Graham, Steve Carr, Griffin Dunne, Steve Brill, James Duffy, Jonathan van Tulleken, Elizabeth Banks, Patrik Forsberg, Brett Ratner, Rusty Cundieff, James Gunn
Description: An eye-popping cast stars in this sketch-comedy collage, the new millennium's homage to classic anthology films like The Kentucky Fried Movie.
A temporary personal chef, a terminally ill single mother and her young daughter form an unlikely bond that redefines the meaning of family.
After inheriting a media empire, humble Longfellow Deeds moves to the Big Apple – where a reporter and a company bigwig are waiting to pounce on him.

Titles: Mr. Gaga: A True Story of Love and Dance
Description: World-renowned choreographer Ohad Naharin is profiled in this vivid documentary that mixes rehearsal footage with insights about his influence.
When a young man ignores a feng shui master’s warning and decides to marry before turning 30, a series of mishaps begins to curse his life.
When a self-help author learns that his mother has fallen for his sadistic high school gym teacher, he tries to put a stop to their budding romance.
A successful advertising agency executive falls asleep on an airplane and wakes up in an alternate universe as a stay-at-home mom with three kids.
Two Mississippi teens meet peculiar drifter Mud and get caught up in his web of tall tales about lost love, crimes of passion and bounty hunters.
Samir must overcome a hostile horoscope, a hot temper and a determined rival to win the heart of Rani, the love of his life.
When the old guardian of the moon retires, the mischievous Mune is chosen as his successor, but he worries he's not up to the job.
In the middle of their global tour, the Muppets inadvertently get mixed up in a perilous drama involving a gang of international jewel thieves.
A mild-mannered office drone plucks a Halloween party invitation off the street and suddenly finds himself the main event at a "murder party."
Marlon Brando gives a nuanced performance as the aristocratic Lt. Fletcher Christian, an officer aboard the HMS Bounty who leads a mutiny against the ship's tyrannical Capt. Bligh.

Titles: My Babysitter's a Vampire: The Movie
Description: When their parents head out for the evening, Ethan and his little sister get the babysitter of their nightmares: a fledgling vampire named Sarah.
After being diagnosed HIV-positive, a champion swimmer is disowned and harassed by all except his loving sister and loyal boyfriend.
After the sudden loss of her husband, a mother has a crisis of faith and struggles to keep her life together for the sake of her daughter and herself.
Relocated to a new post and struggling to adjust, a police officer further complicates his life by falling for a woman he has little in common with.

Titles: My Entire High School Sinking Into the Sea
Description: After an earthquake sends their school building drifting into the sea, a group of high-schoolers struggles to survive and overcome clique wars.
A recently dumped attorney hires a psychic to help her win back her boyfriend. Things take an unexpected turn when another ex re-enters the picture.
A 9-year-old boy finds his life upended when he's sent to live in an orphanage in this stop-motion animated tale of loss, friendship and young love.

Titles: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Friendship Games
Description: Rainbow Dash, Applejack and friends compete against Crystal Prep Academy and their lead athlete, this world's Twilight Sparkle, in sporting events.

Titles: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks
Description: Rainbow Dash, Applejack, Pinkie Pie, Rarity and Fluttershy plan to perform with their new band at the Canterlot High musical showcase.
After the untimely demise of her first three husbands, a stoic single mom is left to raise twelve children on her own and provide for her big family.
A brainy private school student is transferred to a far less elite institution, where he must fend off classmates who settle scores with fistfights.
After speaking with former Scientology members and being stonewalled by higher-ups, filmmaker Louis Theroux hires actors to re-create alleged events.
A former defense attorney finds herself back in court when she and her husband are sued for medical emancipation by their 11-year-old daughter.
A bullied student forms a bond with the leader of a youth gang and discovers the power and meaning of true friendship.
While filming a movie in England, Hollywood icon Marilyn Monroe slips away with a young Brit for a week of self-discovery and frivolity.
A man finds his marriage to a dedicated women's rights activist facing some unexpected challenges over her commitment to the cause.
After losing her father, a young woman moves to the city to earn money. When she finds a job at a mysterious bungalow, her worst nightmares come true.
When Ignacio learns of an orphanage's financial woes, he pitches in to help – by disguising himself and joining the professional wrestling circuit.
This documentary examines the naked yoga gurus of India whose devout spiritual practice connects them to the eternal, transcending the material world.
Recently paralyzed in a devastating car accident, Dana begins to suspect a dark and sinister force may be lurking within her hospital room.
Scientists and animal keepers fight to save an orphaned baby elephant at a rescue camp in Botswana while struggling to defend its entire species.
While loyally defending his boss from mobsters trying to kill him, a naive, hotel bellboy discovers the family he never knew he had.
Aimless valet driver Steven Bassem can't find the motivation to get a better job, even when his fractious immigrant family starts falling apart.
Mistakenly accused of an attack on the Fourth Raikage, ninja Naruto is imprisoned in the impenetrable Hozuki Castle and his powers are sealed.
Chile's Natalia Valdebenito hits Santiago's Teatro Caupolicán with a one-woman show steeped in irony, a dash of improv and her own personal style.
Three former military operatives offer disturbing, firsthand accounts of the deadly impact that U.S. drone warfare has had on civilians overseas.

In this parody of the Lethal Weapon franchise, criminals murder a detective and steal her prized evidence: microfilm with a recipe for cocaine cookies. Luckily, loose-cannon cop Jack Colt and his by-the-book partner, Wes Luger, are on the case.
Narrated by Robert Redford, this documentary tours the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's great parks.
Modern treasure hunters search for a chest of riches rumored to have been stashed away by George Washington, Thomas Jefferson and Benjamin Franklin.
A veteran Shakespearean actor steps off the stage and into the painful tragedy of old age, facing ungrateful family and his fleeting legacy.
The biggest pranksters on YouTube – VitalyzdTV, Dennis Roady and Roman Atwood – turn Hollywood into "Prankwood" with their most over-the-top stunts.
As the new kid, a shy high school senior finds himself tormented by all his peers except one. But his new friend has a dark, infectious outlook.
Shocking footage shows Nazi concentration camps after liberation, including Buchenwald and Ohrdruf, where Gen. Eisenhower ordered local Nazis to tour.
When a Chilean policeman vows to find and capture leftist poet Pablo Neruda, a game of cat and mouse ensues that tests both their wills.
As his father sits behind bars, a young man is lured into Los Angeles' merciless drug world and forced to choose between God and gang life.
When bickering teenage twins accidentally land in the middle of a criminal operation, they'll have to work together to get themselves out of trouble.
This intimate portrait sheds light on the trauma experienced and strength displayed by those affected by the 2012 massacre in Newtown, Connecticut.
Las Vegas magician Cris can see a few minutes into the future and an FBI agent wants his help thwarting a nuclear attack.
With numbers written on a doll as their only clue, three officers of the law track down a psychotic killer, unearthing dark secrets along the way.
A teen fresh out of juvenile detention tries to rescue her sister from foster care in order to exact revenge on their father for their mother's murder.
A pair of young environmentalists enlist the help of an ex-military explosives expert to carry out a dangerous act of eco-terrorism.
A young hustler finds success trolling the streets of Los Angeles to film disasters and death. But the darkness he captures starts to take hold of him.
When a hurricane hits a coastal North Carolina inn and strands the only guest, surgeon Paul Flanner, a young woman's life changes forever.
After a prank goes sideways, three buddies find their relationships  – with women and each other – tested in unexpected ways.
A woman enters a quirky mental health clinic after attempting suicide upon finding out her husband is having an affair with her best friend.
Kate, an uptight chef, finds her life turned upside down when her sister dies in a car accident and she becomes her niece's sole guardian.

Titles: Norm of the North: Family Vacation
Description: Stressed by his duties as king and father, Norm must secretly find his stolen crown while taking his family on a much-needed vacation.

Titles: Norm of the North: Keys to the Kingdom
Description: When Norm the polar bear is framed for a crime he didn’t commit, his friends step up to help him clear his name.

Titles: Norm of the North: King Sized Adventure
Description: Before planning an awesome wedding for his grandfather, a polar bear king must take back a stolen artifact from an evil archaeologist first.
An 18-year-old struggling to understand her best friend's suicide talks to teenagers who have grappled with mental illness and suicidal thoughts.
Astrophysicists show how black holes might hold answers to how the universe evolved, leading to life on Earth and, ultimately, the human race.
Thirty years after Chernobyl’s nuclear disaster, engineers race against time to complete a new dome to contain the reactor’s lethal radiation.
The chariot dominated Chinese warfare for millennia. Now, a team of experts is building their own and unlocking its many secrets.
Drilling into the impact crater of the asteroid that wiped out the dinosaurs, a group of scientists unearths new evidence about the catastrophic event.
After decades of amazing discoveries, spacecraft Cassini embarks on its final – and most daring – mission: a dive below Saturn’s rings.
Scientists investigate Earth’s climate machine, looking for clues across the globe, from Greenland’s ice sheet to the desert of Australia.
Scientists reveal how the 2017 solar eclipse provided new clues into how the sun works, from its scorching atmosphere to its deadly solar storms.
From huge tusks to giant horns, some animals sport weaponry that’s larger than life. Researchers explain the science behind this biological arms race.
During risky expeditions in an underwater cave, scientists unearth a 13,000-year-old skeleton to gain insight into the earliest known humans in America.
At a former Nazi execution site in Lithuania, an international team of archaeologists searches for a lost escape tunnel dug by Jewish prisoners.
Scientists research the world’s deadliest hurricane, trying to understand what this 18th-century storm could tell us about our own future.
Evidence of a mysterious medieval famine leads researchers on a quest for one of the deadliest volcanoes in human history.
This documentary details how the water disaster in Flint, Michigan happened, its lasting effects, and the lengthy efforts it took to correct it.
With the science of forecasting flourishing, this documentary explores how predictions inform our lives and statistics and algorithms' reliability.

Titles: NOVA: Secrets of the Shining Knight
Description: A master armorer and his team recreate parts of a knight's medieval armor and test its strength while rediscovering centuries-old metalworking secrets.
An international team of rescue workers race to save 12 young soccer players and their coach trapped in a flooded cave in Thailand.
Two adventurous pilots attempt to fly around the world without using any fuel, relying only on the power of the sun.
With access to the scientists and engineers responsible for the Curiosity rover's on-the-ground experiments, NOVA captures its landing on Mars.
Dissatisfied with the police’s progress, a teen and his best friend investigate their classmate's murder, treading down a dark path to the uneasy truth.
Waxing nostalgic about the bittersweet passage from childhood to puberty, four childhood girlfriends recall the magical summer of 1970.

Titles: Now More Than Ever: The History of Chicago
Description: This rockumentary tells the behind-the-scenes story of the Hall-of-Fame band Chicago, from their jazz-rock fusion roots to chart-topping pop hits.
Raised by his aunt since he was a young boy, charismatic John Lennon is suddenly reunited with his mother, Julia, which ignites a bitter battle.
Guided by survivors' testimonies, this documentary explores the history and meaning of the numbers tattooed on the bodies of Auschwitz prisoners.

Titles: Numero Zero. The Roots of Italian Rap
Description: In the '90s, the explosive popularity of hip-hop music in Italy impacts the nation's character while creating a new kind of renegade artist.
A self-diagnosed nymphomaniac reveals a lifetime of sexual experiences to a man who saves her from being beaten in an alley.
The second half of Lars von Trier's epic follows Joe as her reignited sex addiction destroys her family and thrusts her toward a surprising new trade.
This film details the rise of British rock group Oasis and the creativity and chaos that brothers Noel and Liam Gallagher brought to the iconic band.
After being fired from her job and dumped by her cheating boyfriend, a comedian has a one-night stand. Weeks later, she finds out she's pregnant.
This documentary examines the vital role water plays in human existence and the cause-and-effect interplay between oceans and the environment.
When aliens take over their small Australian town, a modest group of survivors must unite to fend off their otherworldly intruders.
Frank Sinatra leads an all-star cast as Danny Ocean, who decides to knock over a few casinos on the Las Vegas Strip with his buddies.
This entry in the all-star caper franchise finds debonair con man Danny Ocean and his gang taking revenge on a double-crossing Las Vegas kingpin.
Danny Ocean reunites with his old flame and the rest of his merry band of thieves in a caper covering three huge heists in Rome, Paris and Amsterdam.
Fed up with the uselessness of their degrees and swayed by a TV commercial, two Spaniards head to Berlin for work but find it not quite as advertised.
